#Use the plot() function to produce diagnostic plots of the least squares regression fit. Comment on any problems you see with the fit
plot(lr_Auto)

From residual we can use our linear model and not a non-linear model (residuals are closed to y=0 line). We have some instances with high residual vs fittet value (Outlier)>387,327,323 and others (Standardize residual >3 we classified an outlier). SR(Standardize residual) = 2 >We have residuals!! We have an istance with high std residuals and high leverage!!> 328

Remember: points with high residuals (outliers) dont affect linear regression shape but the RSE (Residual Sum of Error). Point with high leverage affect the linear regression shape. Points with high residuals and leverage are the worst!!!
